_FINAL_SETUP.md`. I am now moving on to validating the Support Tickets item types.\n\n\n**Validating All Item Types**\n\nI've just finished verifying the primary keys and GSI1 indexes for Support Tickets and Governance Items within the `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` table. The keys in the seed script align perfectly with the documented schema for all item types, confirming the data seeding consistency. I have completed my key verification. My current focus shifts to the goal of the seed script as a whole.\n\n\n**Defining Seed Scope**\n\nI'm now clarifying the scope of the seeding process. I plan to focus on seeding users with the roles `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` exclusively, and 2 representative clients. I'll include corresponding projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, tickets, and governance items for those clients. I will not be using fake real client names or logos. I'll also document the seed credentials in the Phase 6 documentation, and ensure that the seed script is idempotent and safe to rerun.\n\n\n**Confirming Seed User Roles**\n\nI'm now double-checking the user roles in my seed data. I'm verifying that the seeding script strictly includes `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` roles, as planned. I will also be seeding 2 representative clients, and I have confirmed the client ids as `1` and `2`, respectively.\n\n\n"}}
